FBIS4-63935 "drsov102_s_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 Georgia Shevardnadze Extends State of Emergency in W. Georgia Shevardnadze Extends State of Emergency in W. Georgia LD2505194894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1826 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505194894 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze today signed a decree to prolong the state of emergency in ten districts of West Georgia until July 23. The state of emergency was imposed last December following an aggravation of the criminal situation. Shevardnadze asked the Georgian parliament to approve his decree.
